comments.body:
@rhatdan the purpose of this command is to apply patch file to a container mounted file system.
In other words applying a patch on a container directly from host.

Yeah docker doesn't have any equivalent.

@rhatdan @baude @mheon @giuseppe before spend my time on these changes I want to be sure the libpod team want to adopt these changes.

@giuseppe doesn't want to patch live containers and so suggest to leave these changes (@giuseppe  I'm right?).

I personaly propose these changes due to debug sessions on openstack where we need to patch containers file with payload to test fix and other stuff so I guess this kind of command can be useful and can allow user to save few times. 

Thoughts?
